race.comment: IL PASSERO (7) rates well and is better suited at this level. Has been caught wide at Warwick Farm his last two, but went close at Canterbury prior, and that reads well. The in-form Mitchell rides and he deserves another chance. BROADWAY BOUNCER (1) settled back first up and impressed when beaten less than 1L in a 72 at Warwick Farm. Proven second-up and he has more to give. Has a low gate and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. A serious player. CLOSE ENCOUNTER (5) wasn't beaten far at Rosehill in a 72 and was a big 68 winner at Kembla Grange. Has a handy gate here and the 3kg sees him well placed.  ATHENA'S TREASURE (9) went to Randwick seeking the hat-trick off a heavily bet country win and didn't get into it from the 14 gate. Peaks here and maps better. On the up, and has to be considered. COYOTE (10) resumes and has the ability. The betting will be key.
